  "explanation": "The defendant, an accountant, abused a position of trust to embezzle $25,000 from their employer. While this breach of fiduciary duty is a serious offense, several mitigating factors have been taken into account. Specifically, the defendant has no prior criminal history and has made a good-faith effort to remedy the harm by partially paying back the embezzled funds. The outburst from the courtroom spectator was inappropriate and played no role in determining this sentence. Weighing the need for deterrence and accountability against the defendant's clean record and partial restitution, a sentence of 6 months of incarceration is deemed appropriate and sufficient.",
  "verdict": 6
}
